To add user identity information in the context of IBM Cloud App ID, you can update the user's profile with their identity attributes. Here's an example using the App ID API:

```bash
curl --request PUT https://<region>.appid.cloud.ibm.com/management/v4/<tenantID>/users/<userID>/profile \
--header 'Authorization: Bearer <IAMToken>' \
--header 'Content-Type: application/json' \
-d '{
"profile": {
"identities": [
{
"identityProvider": "ibm",
"providerUserId": "their-ibm-id",
"attributes": {
"email": "user@example.com",
"name": "John Doe"
}
}
]
}
}'
```

Replace `<region>`, `<tenantID>`, `<userID>`, and `<IAMToken>` with your specific details. The `identityProvider` is the authentication provider, such as "ibm", "google", or "facebook". `providerUserId` is the user's unique identifier in the authentication provider system. Add the user's email and name in the `attributes` section.

For more information, refer to the App ID API documentation: [App ID API documentation](https://cloud.ibm.com/apidocs/app-id#update-a-profile)
